#MEM id=rules source=/root/yvon/agent-department/Technical/dev/skills/design-and-build/vercel-react-best-practices/rules/js-cache-storage.md
M|rules|title: Cache Storage API Calls
M|rules|impact: LOW-MEDIUM
M|rules|impactDescription: reduces expensive I/O
M|rules|tags: javascript, localStorage, storage, caching, performance
M|rules|`localStorage`, `sessionStorage`, and `doc.cookie` are synchronous and expensive. Cache reads in mem.
M|rules|**Incorrect (reads storage on every call):**
M|rules|```typescript
M|rules|function getTheme() {
M|rules|return localStorage.getItem('theme') ?? 'light'
M|rules|}
M|rules|// Called 10 times = 10 storage reads
M|rules|```
M|rules|**Correct (Map cache):**
M|rules|```typescript
M|rules|const storageCache = new Map<string, string | null>()
M|rules|function getLocalStorage(key: string) {
M|rules|if (!storageCache.has(key)) {
M|rules|storageCache.set(key, localStorage.getItem(key))
M|rules|}
M|rules|return storageCache.get(key)
M|rules|}
M|rules|function setLocalStorage(key: string, value: string) {
M|rules|localStorage.setItem(key, value)
M|rules|storageCache.set(key, value)  // keep cache in sync
M|rules|}
M|rules|```
M|rules|Use a Map (not a hook) so it works everywhere: utilities, event handlers, not just React components.
M|rules|**Cookie caching:**
M|rules|```typescript
M|rules|let cookieCache: Record<string, string> | null = null
M|rules|function getCookie(name: string) {
M|rules|if (!cookieCache) {
M|rules|cookieCache = Object.fromEntries(
M|rules|doc.cookie.split('; ').map(c => c.split('='))
M|rules|)
M|rules|}
M|rules|return cookieCache[name]
M|rules|}
M|rules|```
M|rules|**Important (invalidate on external changes):**
M|rules|If storage can change externally (another tab, server-set cookies), invalidate cache:
M|rules|```typescript
M|rules|window.addEventListener('storage', (e) => {
M|rules|if (e.key) storageCache.delete(e.key)
M|rules|})
M|rules|doc.addEventListener('visibilitychange', () => {
M|rules|if (doc.visibilityState === 'visible') {
M|rules|storageCache.clear()
M|rules|}
M|rules|})
M|rules|```